    <h1>Working with Hyperlinks in HTML</h1>

    <p>This is a basic example showing how to use the <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> tag with <code>href</code> and <code>target</code> attributes.</p>

    <h2>Example Links:</h2>

    <!-- Opens in the same tab -->
    <p>
        <a href="https://www.wikipedia.org" target="_self">Open Wikipedia in the same tab (_self)</a>
    </p>

    <!-- Opens in a new tab -->
    <p>
        <a href="https://www.google.com" target="_blank">Open Google in a new tab (_blank)</a>
    </p>

    <!-- Opens in a new window or tab depending on browser -->
    <p>
        <a href="https://www.openai.com" target="_blank">Open OpenAI in a new tab (_blank)</a>
    </p>

    <!-- Opens in the parent frame -->
    <p>
        <a href="https://www.example.com" target="_parent">Open Example in the parent frame (_parent)</a>
    </p>

    <!-- Opens in the full body of the window -->
    <p>
        <a href="https://www.bbc.com" target="_top">Open BBC in the full window (_top)</a>
    </p>

</body>
</html>
